K. Independent of whether the interpretation of the IDV seen in\nthe VLBI core is source intrinsic or extrinsic a lower limit of T_B > 2x10^12 K\nis obtained by model fitting of the VLBI-core. Our results show that future\nVSOP2 observations should be accompanied by a single dish monitoring not only\nto discriminate between source-extrinsic and source-intrinsic effects but to\nallow also a proper calibration and interpretation of ultra-high resolution\nVSOP2 images.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 26 Feb 2008 16:03:07 GMT"}],"update_date":"2008-02-27"}
